init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: reading is always better than listening.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are fully immersed in the author's words.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: With an audiobook you get none of that.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: With an audiobook, you get distracted.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Reading takes time but it's so worth the time you spend to just sit there and enjoy reading.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I think it's important to enjoy the experience of reading.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Obviously, audiobooks aren't going anywhere anytime soon but it's nice to detach from that world for awhile.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It feels nicer and I have better interactions with an actual book.
